{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"You know, there's a small country nestled in the Himalayan Mountains,"},{"time":5000,"text":"far from these beautiful mountains, where the people"},{"time":7000,"text":"of the Kingdom of Bhutan have decided to do something different,"},{"time":10000,"text":"which is to measure their gross national happiness"},{"time":13000,"text":"rather than their gross national product."},{"time":15000,"text":"And why not?"},{"time":17000,"text":"After all, happiness is not just a privilege for the lucky few,"},{"time":21000,"text":"but a fundamental human right for all."},{"time":24000,"text":"And what is happiness?"},{"time":26000,"text":"Happiness is the freedom of choice."},{"time":28000,"text":"The freedom to chose where to live,"},{"time":30000,"text":"what to do, what to buy, what to sell,"},{"time":33000,"text":"from whom, to whom, when and how."},{"time":37000,"text":"Where does choice come from?"},{"time":40000,"text":"And who gets to express it, and how do we express it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":43000,"text":"Well, one way to express choice is through the market."},{"time":48000,"text":"Well-functioning markets provide choices, and ultimately,"},{"time":51000,"text":"the ability to express one's pursuit for happiness."},{"time":56000,"text":"The great Indian economist, Amartya Sen, was awarded the Nobel prize"},{"time":63000,"text":"for demonstrating that famine is not so much about"},{"time":66000,"text":"the availability of food supply, but rather the ability to acquire"},{"time":70000,"text":"or entitle oneself to that food through the market."},{"time":74000,"text":"In 1984, in what can only be considered one of the"},{"time":78000,"text":"greatest crimes of humanity, nearly one million people died of starvation"},{"time":82000,"text":"in my country of birth, Ethiopia."},{"time":84000,"text":"Not because there was not enough food --"},{"time":86000,"text":"because there was actually a surplus of food"},{"time":89000,"text":"in the fertile regions of the south parts of the country --"},{"time":93000,"text":"but because in the north, people could not access"},{"time":95000,"text":"or entitle themselves to that food."},{"time":97000,"text":"That was a turning point for my life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99000,"text":"Most Africans today, by far, are farmers."},{"time":102000,"text":"And most of Africa's farmers are, by and large,"},{"time":106000,"text":"small farmers in terms of land that they operate, and very, very small"},{"time":110000,"text":"farmers in terms of the capital they have at their disposal."},{"time":114000,"text":"African agriculture today is among, or is, the most under-capitalized in the world."},{"time":120000,"text":"Only seven percent of arable land in Africa is irrigated,"},{"time":125000,"text":"compared to 40 percent in Asia."},{"time":127000,"text":"African farmers only use some 22 kilograms of fertilizer per hectare,"},{"time":134000,"text":"compared to 144 in Asia."},{"time":138000,"text":"Road density is six times greater in Asia than it is in rural Africa."},{"time":143000,"text":"There are eight times more tractors in Latin America,"},{"time":146000,"text":"and three times more tractors in Asia, than in Africa."},{"time":151000,"text":"The small farmer in Africa today lives a life without much choice,"},{"time":155000,"text":"and therefore without much freedom."},{"time":157000,"text":"His livelihood is predetermined"},{"time":159000,"text":"by the conditions of grinding poverty."},{"time":162000,"text":"He comes to the market when prices are lowest,"},{"time":165000,"text":"with the meager fruits of his hard labor, just after the harvest,"},{"time":168000,"text":"because he has no choice."},{"time":170000,"text":"She comes back to the market"},{"time":173000,"text":"some months later, when prices are highest, in what we call"},{"time":176000,"text":"the lean season -- when food is scarce --"},{"time":179000,"text":"because she has to feed her family and has no choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185000,"text":"The real question is, how can markets be developed in rural Africa"},{"time":190000,"text":"to harness the power of innovation and entrepreneurship"},{"time":193000,"text":"that we know exists?"},{"time":195000,"text":"Another notable economist, Theodore Schultz,"},{"time":200000,"text":"in 1974 won the Nobel prize for demonstrating that farmers"},{"time":204000,"text":"are efficient, but poor."},{"time":206000,"text":"Meaning, in fact, that farmers are rational"},{"time":209000,"text":"and profit-minded just like everybody else."},{"time":211000,"text":"Well, we don't need, now,"},{"time":214000,"text":"any more Nobel prizes to know that farmers want a fair shake"},{"time":217000,"text":"at the market and want to make money, just like everyone else."},{"time":221000,"text":"And one thing is clear, which is at least now we know"},{"time":225000,"text":"that Africa is open for business."},{"time":227000,"text":"And that business is agriculture."},{"time":231000,"text":"Over two decades ago, the world insisted to Africa that markets"},{"time":235000,"text":"must be liberalized, that economies must be structurally adjusted."},{"time":240000,"text":"This meant that governments were to remove themselves"},{"time":242000,"text":"from the business of buying and selling --"},{"time":244000,"text":"which they did rather inefficiently --"},{"time":246000,"text":"and let the private market do its magic."},{"time":249000,"text":"Well, what happened over the last 25 years?"},{"time":252000,"text":"Did Africa feed itself?"},{"time":254000,"text":"Did our farmers turn into highly productive commercial actors?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"I think we're all in this room,"},{"time":261000,"text":"probably, because we know that, in fact, Africa is the only region"},{"time":265000,"text":"in the world where hunger and malnutrition are projected to go up"},{"time":269000,"text":"over the next 10 years,"},{"time":271000,"text":"where the food import bill is now double"},{"time":274000,"text":"what it was 20 years ago,"},{"time":276000,"text":"where food production per capita has"},{"time":280000,"text":"stagnated, and where fertilizer use has declined rather than increased."},{"time":286000,"text":"So why didn't agriculture markets perform to expectations?"},{"time":289000,"text":"The market reforms prompted by the West --"},{"time":291000,"text":"and I've spent some 15 years traveling around the continent"},{"time":296000,"text":"doing research on agricultural markets, and have interviewed"},{"time":299000,"text":"traders in 10 to 15 countries in this continent, hundreds of traders --"},{"time":304000,"text":"trying to understand what went wrong with our market reform."},{"time":309000,"text":"And it seems to me that the reforms might have"},{"time":313000,"text":"thrown the baby out with the bath water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315000,"text":"Like its agriculture,"},{"time":317000,"text":"Africa's markets are highly under-capitalized and inefficient."},{"time":321000,"text":"We know from our work around the continent"},{"time":323000,"text":"that transaction costs of reaching the market,"},{"time":326000,"text":"and the risks of transacting in rural, agriculture markets,"},{"time":330000,"text":"are extremely high."},{"time":332000,"text":"In fact, only one third of agricultural output"},{"time":335000,"text":"produced in Africa even reaches the market."},{"time":338000,"text":"Africa's markets are weak not only because of weak infrastructure"},{"time":342000,"text":"in terms of roads and telecommunications, but also because"},{"time":346000,"text":"of the virtual absence of necessary market institutions, such as"},{"time":350000,"text":"market information, grades and standards,"},{"time":354000,"text":"and reliable ways to connect buyers and sellers."},{"time":357000,"text":"Because of this, commodity buyers and sellers typically transact in small circles,"},{"time":362000,"text":"in narrow networks of people they know and trust."},{"time":366000,"text":"And because of that, as grain changes hands --"},{"time":370000,"text":"and I've measured that it changes hands four, five times in"},{"time":374000,"text":"its trajectory from the farmer to the consumer --"},{"time":377000,"text":"every time it changes hands -- and I've seen this all over rural Africa --"},{"time":381000,"text":"it also changes sacks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383000,"text":"And I thought that was incredibly peculiar."},{"time":385000,"text":"And really realized that that was because -- as traders would tell me"},{"time":388000,"text":"over and over -- that's the only way people know what they're getting"},{"time":391000,"text":"in terms of the quantity and the product quality."},{"time":395000,"text":"And that actually has huge implications"},{"time":398000,"text":"for the ability of markets to quickly respond to price signals,"},{"time":403000,"text":"and situations where there are deficits, for example."},{"time":406000,"text":"It also has very high cost implications."},{"time":409000,"text":"I have measured that 26 percent of the marketing margin"},{"time":412000,"text":"is simply due to the fact that, because of the absence"},{"time":414000,"text":"of grades and standards and market information,"},{"time":418000,"text":"sacks have to be constantly changed."},{"time":421000,"text":"And this leads to very high handling costs."},{"time":424000,"text":"For their part, small farmers, who produce the bulk of our agricultural output in Africa,"},{"time":429000,"text":"come to the market with virtually no information at all -- blind --"},{"time":433000,"text":"trusting that they're going to have"},{"time":436000,"text":"some sort of demand for their produce,"},{"time":439000,"text":"and completely at the mercy of the merchants"},{"time":443000,"text":"in the only market, the nearest local market they know --"},{"time":447000,"text":"where they're unable to negotiate better prices or reduce their risk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450000,"text":"Speaking of risk, we have seen that price volatility"},{"time":454000,"text":"of food crops in Africa is the highest in the world."},{"time":456000,"text":"In Africa, small farmers bear the brunt of this risk."},{"time":460000,"text":"In fact, in my view, there is no region of the world and no period in history"},{"time":469000,"text":"that farmers have been expected to bear the kind of market risk"},{"time":470000,"text":"that Africa's farmers have to bear."},{"time":473000,"text":"And in my view, there is simply no place in the world"},{"time":475000,"text":"that has grown its agriculture on the kind of risk"},{"time":479000,"text":"that our farmers in Africa today face."},{"time":482000,"text":"In Ethiopia, for example, the variation in maize prices"},{"time":486000,"text":"from year to year is as much as 50 percent annually."},{"time":489000,"text":"This kind of market risk is mind-boggling, and has direct implications"},{"time":493000,"text":"for not only the incentives of farmers to invest"},{"time":497000,"text":"in higher productivity technology, such as modern seeds and fertilizers,"},{"time":502000,"text":"but also direct implications for food security."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505000,"text":"To give you an example, between 2001 and 2002,"},{"time":509000,"text":"Ethiopian maize farmers produced two years of bumper harvest."},{"time":512000,"text":"That in turn, because of the weak marketing system,"},{"time":515000,"text":"led to an 80 percent collapse in maize prices in the country."},{"time":520000,"text":"This made it unprofitable for some farmers to even harvest the grain from the fields."},{"time":525000,"text":"And we calculated that some 300,000 tons of grain"},{"time":528000,"text":"was left in the fields to rot in early 2002."},{"time":532000,"text":"Not six months later, in July 2002, Ethiopia announced a major food crisis,"},{"time":538000,"text":"to the same proportions as 1984: 14 million people at risk of starvation."},{"time":543000,"text":"What also happened that year"},{"time":546000,"text":"is in the areas where there were good rains, and where farmers"},{"time":550000,"text":"had previously produced surplus grain, farmers had decided"},{"time":554000,"text":"to withdraw from the fertilizer market, not use fertilizer"},{"time":558000,"text":"and actually had dropped their use of fertilizer by 27 percent."},{"time":562000,"text":"This is a tragic example of arrested development,"},{"time":568000,"text":"or a budding green revolution stopped in its tracks."},{"time":571000,"text":"And this is not just specific to Ethiopia,"},{"time":573000,"text":"but happens over and over, all over Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577000,"text":"Well, I'm not here today to lament about the situation, or wring my hands."},{"time":584000,"text":"I am here to tell you that change is in the air."},{"time":588000,"text":"Africa today is not the Africa waiting for aid solutions,"},{"time":592000,"text":"or cookie-cutter foreign expert policy prescriptions."},{"time":596000,"text":"Africa has learned, or is learning somewhat slowly,"},{"time":600000,"text":"that markets don't happen by themselves."},{"time":603000,"text":"In the 1980s, it was very fashionable"},{"time":606000,"text":"to talk about getting prices right."},{"time":608000,"text":"There was a very influential book about that,"},{"time":610000,"text":"which was mainly about getting governments out of the market."},{"time":614000,"text":"We now recognize that getting markets right is about not just"},{"time":618000,"text":"price incentives, but also investing in the right infrastructure"},{"time":622000,"text":"and the appropriate and necessary institutions to create"},{"time":625000,"text":"the conditions to unleash the power of innovation in the market."},{"time":630000,"text":"When conditions are right, we know and see"},{"time":633000,"text":"that that innovation is ready to explode in rural Africa,"},{"time":637000,"text":"just like anywhere else."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639000,"text":"Nearly three years ago, I decided to leave my comfortable job"},{"time":643000,"text":"as a World Bank senior economist in Washington"},{"time":646000,"text":"and come back to my country of birth, Ethiopia,"},{"time":648000,"text":"after nearly 30 years abroad."},{"time":650000,"text":"I did so for a simple reason."},{"time":652000,"text":"After having spent more than a decade"},{"time":656000,"text":"understanding, studying, and trying to convince policymakers and donors"},{"time":661000,"text":"about what was wrong with Africa's agricultural markets,"},{"time":663000,"text":"I decided it was time to do something about it."},{"time":667000,"text":"I currently lead, in Ethiopia, an exciting new initiative"},{"time":672000,"text":"to establish the first Ethiopia Commodity Exchange, or ECX."},{"time":676000,"text":"Now, the commodity exchange itself, that concept,"},{"time":680000,"text":"is not new to the world."},{"time":682000,"text":"In fact, in 1848, 82 grain merchants and farmers got together"},{"time":686000,"text":"in a small town at the crossroads of the Illinois River and Lake Michigan"},{"time":691000,"text":"to establish a way to trade better amongst themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697000,"text":"That was, of course, the birth of the Chicago Board of Trade,"},{"time":701000,"text":"which is the most famous commodity exchange in the world."},{"time":705000,"text":"The Chicago Board of Trade was established then"},{"time":707000,"text":"for precisely the same reasons"},{"time":709000,"text":"that our farmers today would benefit from a commodity exchange."},{"time":714000,"text":"In the American Midwest, farmers used to load grain onto barges"},{"time":717000,"text":"and send it upriver to the Chicago market."},{"time":720000,"text":"But once it arrived, if no buyer was to be found,"},{"time":725000,"text":"or if prices suddenly dropped, farmers would incur tremendous losses."},{"time":730000,"text":"And in fact, would even dump the grain in Lake Michigan,"},{"time":732000,"text":"rather than spend more money transporting it back to their farms."},{"time":736000,"text":"Well, the need to avoid these huge risks and tremendous losses"},{"time":741000,"text":"led to the birth of the futures market, and the underlying system"},{"time":744000,"text":"of grading grain and receipting -- issuing warehouse receipts"},{"time":748000,"text":"on the basis of which trade could be done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750000,"text":"From there, the greatest innovation of all came about in this market,"},{"time":756000,"text":"which is that buyers and sellers could transact grain"},{"time":759000,"text":"without actually having to physically or visually inspect the grain."},{"time":764000,"text":"That meant that grain could be traded across tremendous distances,"},{"time":767000,"text":"and even across time -- as far forward as 18 months into the future."},{"time":772000,"text":"This innovation is at the heart of the transformation of American agriculture,"},{"time":776000,"text":"and the rise of Chicago to a global market,"},{"time":780000,"text":"agricultural market, superpower from where it was, a small regional town."},{"time":785000,"text":"Now, over the last century,"},{"time":788000,"text":"we tend to think of commodity exchanges as the purview"},{"time":791000,"text":"of Western industrialized countries,"},{"time":793000,"text":"and that the reference prices for cotton, coffee, cocoa --"},{"time":796000,"text":"products produced mainly in the south --"},{"time":799000,"text":"are actually a reference price, or a price discovered in these"},{"time":804000,"text":"organized commodity exchanges in the northern countries."},{"time":808000,"text":"But that is actually changing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":810000,"text":"And we're seeing a shift --"},{"time":812000,"text":"powered mainly because of information technology --"},{"time":815000,"text":"a shift in market dominance towards the emerging markets."},{"time":818000,"text":"And over the last decade, you see that the share of Western exchanges --"},{"time":823000,"text":"and this is the U.S. share of exchanges in the world --"},{"time":829000,"text":"has gone down by nearly half in just the last decade."},{"time":832000,"text":"Similarly, there's been explosive growth in India, for example,"},{"time":836000,"text":"where rural farmers are using exchanges -- growing here"},{"time":840000,"text":"over the last three years by 270 percent a year."},{"time":845000,"text":"This is powered by low-cost VSAT technology,"},{"time":848000,"text":"aggressively trying to reach farmers to bring them into the market."},{"time":852000,"text":"China's Dalian Commodity Exchange, three years ago,"},{"time":856000,"text":"2004, overtook the Chicago Board of Trade to become"},{"time":859000,"text":"the second largest commodity exchange in the world."},{"time":863000,"text":"Now, in Ethiopia, we're in the process of designing"},{"time":867000,"text":"the first organized Ethiopia Commodity Exchange."},{"time":870000,"text":"We're not trying to cut and paste the Chicago model"},{"time":873000,"text":"or the India model, but creating a system uniquely tailored"},{"time":876000,"text":"to Ethiopia's needs and realities,"},{"time":878000,"text":"Ethiopia's small farmers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":880000,"text":"So, the ECX is an Ethiopian exchange for Ethiopia."},{"time":883000,"text":"We're creating a system that serves all market actors,"},{"time":887000,"text":"that creates integrity, trust, efficiency, transparency"},{"time":893000,"text":"and enables small farmers to manage the risks that I have described."},{"time":897000,"text":"In the design of our commodity exchange in Ethiopia,"},{"time":900000,"text":"we've done something rather unique, which is to"},{"time":902000,"text":"take the approach of an integrated perspective,"},{"time":904000,"text":"or what we call the ECX Edge."},{"time":907000,"text":"The ECX Edge pretty much creates the entire ecosystem"},{"time":911000,"text":"in which the market will develop itself."},{"time":914000,"text":"And this is because one of the things we've learned"},{"time":917000,"text":"over the last decade of studying market development in Africa"},{"time":920000,"text":"is that the piecemeal approach does not work."},{"time":923000,"text":"You've got one donor trying to develop market information,"},{"time":926000,"text":"another trying to work on or sponsor grades and standards,"},{"time":930000,"text":"another ICT, and yet another on warehousing, or warehouse receipts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":936000,"text":"In our approach in Ethiopia,"},{"time":938000,"text":"we've decided to put together the entire ecosystem,"},{"time":942000,"text":"or environment, in which trade takes place."},{"time":945000,"text":"That means that the exchange will operate a trading system,"},{"time":949000,"text":"which will initially start as an open outcry,"},{"time":953000,"text":"because we don't think the country's ready for full electronic trading."},{"time":956000,"text":"But at the same time, we'll do something which I think no exchange"},{"time":958000,"text":"in the world has ever done, which is itself to operate something like"},{"time":963000,"text":"an Internet cafe in the rural areas."},{"time":965000,"text":"So that farmers and small traders"},{"time":968000,"text":"can actually come to a terminal center -- what we call"},{"time":971000,"text":"the remote access terminal centers -- and actually,"},{"time":974000,"text":"without having to buy a computer or figure out how to dial up"},{"time":976000,"text":"or any of those things, simply see the trading"},{"time":979000,"text":"that's happening on the Addis Ababa trading floor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":983000,"text":"At the same time, what's very fundamental to this market is that --"},{"time":986000,"text":"and again, an innovation that we've designed for our exchange --"},{"time":990000,"text":"is that the exchange will operate warehouses around the country,"},{"time":993000,"text":"in which grade certification and warehouse receipting will be done."},{"time":997000,"text":"And in turn, we'll operate an in-house clearing system,"},{"time":1000000,"text":"to assure that payment is done appropriately,"},{"time":1004000,"text":"in the right amount and at the right time,"},{"time":1007000,"text":"so that basically, we create trust and integrity in the system."},{"time":1011000,"text":"Obviously, we work with exchange actors,"},{"time":1014000,"text":"and as we're developing the exchange market itself,"},{"time":1017000,"text":"we're also developing the regulatory infrastructure and legal framework,"},{"time":1021000,"text":"the overarching legal framework for making this market work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1024000,"text":"So, in fact, our proclamation"},{"time":1027000,"text":"is going to parliament next month."},{"time":1030000,"text":"What's really important is that the ECX will operate a market information system"},{"time":1035000,"text":"to disseminate prices in real time to farmers around the country,"},{"time":1039000,"text":"using VSAT technology to bring an electronic price dissemination"},{"time":1044000,"text":"directly to farmers."},{"time":1046000,"text":"What this does is transforms, fundamentally,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"the farmers' relationship to the market."},{"time":1052000,"text":"Whereas before the farmer used to think local --"},{"time":1055000,"text":"meaning that he or she would go to the nearest local market,"},{"time":1058000,"text":"eight to 10 kilometers away on average,"},{"time":1060000,"text":"and sell whatever they happened to have,"},{"time":1062000,"text":"without any idea of what the price premium or anything else was --"},{"time":1066000,"text":"now farmers come with knowledge of what prices are at the national market."},{"time":1070000,"text":"And they start to think national, and even global."},{"time":1073000,"text":"They start to make not only commercial marketing decisions,"},{"time":1077000,"text":"but also planting decisions, on the basis of information"},{"time":1080000,"text":"coming from the futures price market."},{"time":1084000,"text":"And they come to the market knowing what grades their products"},{"time":1088000,"text":"will achieve in terms of a price premium."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1091000,"text":"So all of this will transform farmers."},{"time":1093000,"text":"It will also transform the way traders do business."},{"time":1096000,"text":"It will stop them from doing simple, back-to-back, limited arbitrage"},{"time":1102000,"text":"to really thinking strategically about how to move grain"},{"time":1105000,"text":"across long distances from [surplus regions] to [deficit areas]."},{"time":1109000,"text":"Can Ethiopia do this?"},{"time":1112000,"text":"It seems very ambitious."},{"time":1114000,"text":"But it will create new opportunities."},{"time":1116000,"text":"We believe that this initiative requires great political will,"},{"time":1119000,"text":"and we'll have to align the financial sector, as well as the ICT sector,"},{"time":1124000,"text":"and really even the underlying legal framework."},{"time":1128000,"text":"We believe that the winds of change are here, and that we can do it."},{"time":1132000,"text":"ECX is the market for Ethiopia's new millennium,"},{"time":1136000,"text":"which starts in about eight months."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1140000,"text":"The last parliament of our century opened with our president"},{"time":1144000,"text":"announcing to the country that this was the most important"},{"time":1147000,"text":"economic initiative for the country today."},{"time":1149000,"text":"We believe that the stakes are high,"},{"time":1152000,"text":"but that the returns will be even greater."},{"time":1155000,"text":"ECX, moreover, can become a trading platform for a pan-African market"},{"time":1160000,"text":"in agricultural commodities."},{"time":1162000,"text":"Ethiopia's domestic market is about one billion dollars of value."},{"time":1166000,"text":"And we feel that over the next five years,"},{"time":1170000,"text":"if Ethiopia can capture even 40 percent, just 40 percent, of the domestic market,"},{"time":1176000,"text":"and add just 25 percent value to that market, the value of the market doubles."},{"time":1181000,"text":"Ethiopia's agricultural market is 30 percent higher"},{"time":1184000,"text":"than South Africa's grain production,"},{"time":1188000,"text":"and, in fact, Ethiopia is the second largest maize producer in Africa."},{"time":1191000,"text":"So the potential is there."},{"time":1193000,"text":"The will is there."},{"time":1195000,"text":"The commitment is there."},{"time":1197000,"text":"So we feel that we have a winning value proposition"},{"time":1201000,"text":"to transform farmers' choices, to grow our agriculture,"},{"time":1205000,"text":"and to change Africa."},{"time":1207000,"text":"So, we are in the business of finding our happiness."},{"time":1211000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1212000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}